rooms.Name: Park Entrance
rooms.Description:
Before are the massive doors that lead into...

               J U R A S S I C   P A R K ! ! ! ! 

                     W A R N I N G ! ! ! ! 

This area is not for the weak-hearted.  The sights you will see beyond
these doors will amaze you.  Dare you open these doors, you will be
drawn into the past by glimpcing the future!

rooms.Name: Road Through the Jungle
rooms.Description:
As you pass through the massive doors, you hear them slam shut!  You
gulp and ask yourself what have you gotten yourself into?  There is 
nothing else to do but to go on and not look back.  The jungle
growth overflows into the road.  Some of these plants are like none
you have ever seen before.  The air has a thick musty smell to it, 
you feel as if you can almost touch the air!

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
The exit is getting farther and farther away as you travel along this
road.  You see strange creatures dart across your path, appearing from
somewhere in the jungle and then dissapearing back into the jungle on 
the other side of the road.  You chuckle at the sight of these little
creatures and continue to walk on.

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
The jungle acts as a pair of walls on both sides of you.  The jungle
canopy reaches a good 100 feet above you, cutting out the sunlight very
effectively.  You feel a little catostrophic with the jungle all around
you.  The air is thick and has a musty smell to it.

rooms.Name: Fork in the road
rooms.Description:
The road seperates here.  You try to decide which way to go but as you
try to look down the two roads, all you can see is jungle and more
jungle.  You have to make up your mind sometime, why not look at the
sign.  That's what they're there for!

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
A narrow road cuts through the jungle, leading to the helicopter pad.  You
have a gut feeling that something bad is going to happen, almost like you
are being hunted by a fearsome predator.  Your insides churn over, leaving
you sick to your stomach.  The jungle looms over you.  Trapping you
inside of it.

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
A narrow road cuts through the jungle, leading to the helicopter pad.  The
road has taken a sharp turn to the northeast.  You have to be careful not
to get lost in this jungle, there are many dangerous animals that are 
killing for a meal.

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
After almost missing that sharp turn in the road, you continue on your way
to the helicopter landingpad.  All around you, birds are squawking,
making awful noises.  Your spine tingles and the hair on your arms is
standing on end.  Maybe you shouldn't have come to this island for 
vacation.

rooms.Name: A small clearing
rooms.Description:
The road opens up to a small clearing here.  The jungle has been pushed
back by man-made efforts.  There's a little shed in the corner, it 
resembles an outhouse.  You here birds squawking in the trees, making
you nervous.  You have a feeling you are being followed.  Maybe you
should run to catch that helicopter that is waiting for you.

rooms.Name: Helicopter Landingpad
rooms.Description:
You see a great waterfall just to the north of here, it's casting beautiful
rainbows all about here.  This is the only air exit on the island and it is
open only to VIPs, which of course, you're not!  You see a lot of nervous
men standing around scanning the surronding jungle.  They seem as if they
are preparing for an attack of some sorts.  You don't wanna be around for
that!

rooms.Name: Path to the entrance
rooms.Description:
You are getting closer to what you came here for but you also have a soft
fear running around all inside you.  This is where they say the past and
the future collide.  The imbalance could shift at any time and chaos
would gain control of this island.  Your chances of turning back are
decreasing with each step.  If you are up to it, continue on, but if you
are not, turn back and try to catch the boat you came in on.

rooms.Name: The docks
rooms.Description:
This is the only way on and off the island.  If there is a massive
storm, the boats won't come to take you off the islands.  Stuck you'll be!
So make sure that you want to be here, and not at home with your hot 
chocolate and cookies.

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
The jungle acts as a pair of walls on both sides of you.  The jungle 
canopy reaches a good 100 feet above you, cutting out the sunlight very
effectively.  You feel a little catostrophic with the jungle all around
you.  The air is thick and has a musty smell to it.

rooms.Name: Road through the jungle
rooms.Description:
The moist jungle floor sinks under you about an inch.  This is a beautiful
ecosystem.  Extinct plant life all over.  The geneticists have done a 
miraculous job here.  You just can't wait to see the dinosaurs.  There's
a large gate up ahead that looks to be humming.

rooms.Name: Electric Gate
rooms.Description:
You've had your fun, but once you pass on in through these gates,
you will be held reliable.  This electric fence surronds the whole park,
this is the only way through.  So if you feel that you can handle
pre-historic nature, feel free to enter it's domain!

rooms.Name: Intersection
rooms.Description:
This is where you make up your mind.  You're anxious to see all the 
wonders this island holds, but you also want to check out the visitor
center.  What to do?  The question hangs over your head.  You can see
the huge building that is the visitor center just to the north of
these cross roads.  You think it might be rather dangerous to go 
roaming through the park without a guide.

rooms.Name: Road to the Visitor Center
rooms.Description:
This road leads to the visitor center.  You made the right choice of
not roaming through the jungle without a guide.  You can see the jungle
dispersing up ahead.  You feel a new anticipation take over you.  What
new things will you see?  What new feelings will you feel?  Continue
on my friend and find out exactly!

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
This is your first step into the past.  All around you you see plant
life that became extinct millions of years ago.  The smell of this
place is even old.  The oxygen level is higher than normal, making you
a little dizzy.  You here the sounds of extinct creatures all around
you.  You bubble with excitement, yet you are apprehensive to
continue on.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
The Tour Path is a narrow, cutaway dirt road that runs through the
jungle.  The sounds of extinct animals are all around you.  The
moist, oxygen rich air fills your lungs.  You look all around you
for a chance to catch a glimpse of a dinosaur.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
The Tour Path is a narrow, cutaway dirt road that runs through the
jungle.  The sounds of extinct animals are all around you.  The moist,
oxygen rich air fills your lungs.  You look around for a chance to
catch a glimpse of a dinosaur.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
The Tour Path takes a turn here, but off to the left is the 
Dilophosaurs Paddox.  You strain your neck trying to look in to
see one of these pre-historic creatures.  Guess the only way you're
going to see them is if you actually enter the paddox and have a
look around.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You just passed the Dilophosaurs Paddox.  You continue your journey
through the park.  You look around in awe at all the pre-historic
sites.  A thought passes through your mind, should these extinct
creatures be made for your viewing pleasure?  Should man be meddling
with nature?  Should man be playing God?

rooms.Name: Off the Tour Path
rooms.Description:
Aren't you the little rebel?  Going off the Tour Path to go exploring?
There are a bunch of Compys running around.  You wonder why there are
so many of them here.  There's an odd smell in the air.  Welp, since
you're off the Tour Path, you might as well go investigate.

rooms.Name: Dilophosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
You notice a putrid smell as you enter the paddox.  This is the only
carnivore on the tour until you get to the TRex and the Raptors.  This
is the paddox for the ever dangerous Dilophosaur.  Your stomach tells
you you shouldn't have left the Tour Path.  You have entered their
domain, their territory.  Be on your guard and keep your distance.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You continue on your journey through history.  You follow the Tour
Path through Jurassic Park, scanning the jungle for any sign of life,
either friendly dinosaurs or dangerous dinosaurs.

rooms.Name: Dilophosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The putrid smell of decaying flesh invades your nostrils leaving
you sick to your stomach.  You hear the soft hooting sounds of the
ever dangerous Dilophosaur.  Be on your guard and keep your distance
from these dangerous Dilos.

rooms.Name: Dilophosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The putrid smeel of rotting flesh fills your nostrils, making you
sick to your stomach.  You hear the soft hooting sound of the
ever dangerous Dilophosaur.  Keep you distance and always remember
to keep you guard.

rooms.Name: Dilophosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The putrid smell invades your nostrils making you sick to your
stomach.  The jungle is all around you and you hear the soft
hooting of the ever dangerous Dilophosaurs.  Be on you guard,
these dinosaurs aren't friendly.

rooms.Name: The Electric Fence
rooms.Description:
Welp...I guess that's why all those Compys were around.  To eat your
corpse.  Well...what did you expect???  It said electric fence and
you were electrocuted.  So Sorry!

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
The Pteradactyl Aviary is off to the west.  You look up to see these
magnificent animals, but the jungle canopy blocks your view.  You
ponder whether or not to enter the Aviary, but you had better decide
quick before the next tour group comes through!

rooms.Name: Pteradactyl Aviary
rooms.Description:
This is the Pteradactyl Aviary.  It's like normal zoo aviaries except
much larger, mainly because it houses the worlds largest flying 
animal ever to fly in its atmosphere!

rooms.Name: Pteradactyl Aviary
rooms.Description:
This is the Pteradactyl Aviary.  It resembles a normal zoo aviary,
yet it is much much larger.  It has to be to hold these giant flying
dinosaurs.  You look up to spy one of these Pteradactyls, just
remember to keep your mouth shut while looking up!

rooms.Name: Pteradactyl Aviary
rooms.Description:
This is the Pteradactyl Aviary.  It holds the largest flying
animal that the earth has ever known.  You look up and around
to hopefully catch a glimpse of these magnificent flying dinosaurs.
But be careful, they are extremely territorial!

rooms.Name: Pteradactyl Aviary
rooms.Description:
This large aviary holds the massive flying dinosaurs; the Pteradactyl.
You look up to look at these magestic creatures, but you better
watch out, they are extremely territorial, attacking all invaders
of their territory.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You just passed the Pteradactyl Aviary, hope you didn't go in.  Those
guys are rather emphatic about protecting their territory.  You wonder
what's next on the tour and continue on anxiously.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You continue on your journey through time on this dirt road.  You
listen to all the jungle noises as you walk along.  You feel very
alone out here in the jungle.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You continue on your journey through time along this dirt road.  You
listen to all the sounds of the jungle.  You feel very alone out
here on this Tour Path.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
Up ahead you see that you are coming up to another paddox.  You
are very anxious to see more of these wonderous animals.  You feel
almost like running to the next paddox like a child runs from ride to
ride at an amusement park.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
Off to the northwest is the Stegosaurs Paddox.  You remember pictures
of this dinosaur in your old picture books you had as a child.  You
try to catch a peek of one but can't see anything.  You remember that
Stegosaurs were herbivores so you feel kind of safe going off the path
and into the Paddox to have a good look at these ancient animals.

rooms.Name: Stegosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
As you look around, you see a lot of half-eaten plants.  This is
where the Stegosaurs roam.  These mighty beasts pay no attention to
you for you pose no threat to them.  They just continue on with what
they were doing before you interupted them.

rooms.Name: Stegosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
As you look around, you see a lot of half-eaten plants.  This is
where the Stegosaurs roam.  These mighty beasts pay no attention to
you for you pose no threat.  They just continue on with what they
were doing before you intterupted them.

rooms.Name: Stegosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
As you look around, you see a lot of half-eaten plants.  This is 
where the Stegosaurs roam.  These mighty beasts pay no attention to
you for you pose no threat to them.  They just continue on with what
they were doing before you interupted them.

rooms.Name: Stegosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
This is where the Stegosaurs roam.  You see a lot of half-eaten
plants all around.  The Stegosaurs take one look at you and continue
on with what they were doing for you pose no threat to them.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You just passed the Stegosaur Paddox and are happy that you didn't catch
that spiked tail with your gut!  You are in total awe at how wonderful
this park is.  You can't wait to get home to tell your friends, that
is if you do get home.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You walk along the cutaway dirt road observing all the little compies
scuttle about, in and out of the jungle.  You smile at the thought
of being as carefree as those little creatures.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
Up ahead you see the Triceratops Paddox.  You wonder how big those
spikes on their heads really are.  The tour guide says that if you
leave the path one more time that you'll be kicked out of the park.
But, since when do you ever listen?

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
The Triceratops Paddox is just north of here.  Remember what the tour
guide said.  The temptation is there though.  You really want to 
see those Triceratops.  Just let the tour group go on and make it
look like you got lost!

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You just passed the Triceratops Paddox, barely making it out alive
with all of your entrails intact.  Those horns are mighty sharp
and powerful.  You try to calm down and continue on with the
tour

rooms.Name: Triceratops Paddox
rooms.Description:
This is much like the Stegosaurus Paddox except that it houses the
mighty Triceratops.  You look around for them and hope to catch
a good look at one.

rooms.Name: Triceratops Paddox
rooms.Description:
This is much like the Stegosaurus Paddox except that it houses
the mighty Triceratops.  You look and around in hopes of catching
a glimpse of one.

rooms.Name: Triceratops Paddox
rooms.Description:
This is much like the Stegosaurus Paddox except that it houses
the mighty Triceratops.  You look around in hopes of catching
a glimpse of one.

rooms.Name: Triceratops Paddox
rooms.Description:
This is much like the Stegosaurus Paddox except that it houses the
might Triceratops.  You look around in hopes of catching a glimpse
of one of these animals

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You feel like things are getting out of hand.  All of these animals
became extinct for a reason, why should they be back in our modern
day?  You shrug off your feelings and continue on with the tour.

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
The Brontosaurs Paddox is just off to the east.  More scientifically
speaking, these are Hadrosaurs.  But who really cares when you have
a chance at seeing the largest creatures that ever roamed freely
on this planet?

rooms.Name: Tour Path
rooms.Description:
You just passed the Brontosaurs Paddox and feel peaceful after
observing those huge animals.  All of a sudden the hair on the
back of your neck raises as you remember that you haven't
seen the awesomest predator that ever lived yet.  You tremble
uncontrolably but continue on anyway.

rooms.Name: No Turning Back
rooms.Description:
Somethig is dreadfully wrong.  Everything electrical looks like it
is not working.  You want to turn back, but you realize that
that is now impossible.  There's a strange stench in the air and
you feel like you are going to throw up.  Your knees grow weak
and your hands tremble.  You are scared.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  Dinosaurs roam free no longer confined
to their paddoxs.  You feel like you are going to die.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  The dinosaurs roam free no longer confined to
thier paddoxs.  You feel like you are going to die.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  You see the effects directly by looking
to the east.  Maybe that's a way out.  Are you too scared to find
out?  Go take a look.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  Dinosaurs roam free no longer confined
to their paddoxs.  You feel like you are going to die.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  Dinosaurs roam free no longer confined
to thier paddoxs.  You feel like you are going to die.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  You look down and notice that the TRex
paddox seems empty.  You hear the roar of the mighty TRex.  You 
tremble uncontrolably.  What are you going to do?

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  You have now lost all sense of direction
and start to wander around through the jungle wary of hostile
dinosaurs.  You wonder if you'll make it off this island alive.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  You have now lost all sense of direction
and start to wander around through the jungle wary of hostile
dinosaurs.  You wonder if you'll make it off the island alive.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  You have now lost all sense of direction
and start to wander around through the jungle wary of hostile
dinosaurs.  You wonder if you'll make it of this island alive.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
Udder and total chaos.  You have now lost all sense of direction
and start to wander around through the jungle wary of hostile
dinosaurs.  You wonder if you'll make it off this island alive.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
It seems that you have found your way out of the jungle as 
you notice the jungle receding a little.  You feel a sweep of
relieve come over you and continue on to try to get off the
island.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
You look to the west and see a familiar setting and know that
that is your way out.  You look up and wonder what exactly is
up there.  Now your curiosity is getting to you and you must
decide what to do, leave the island, or go look and see what 
is up above you.

rooms.Name: Brontosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The tallest trees on the island are here in the Brontosaurs Paddox,
and why shouldn't they be seeing as these were the largest animals
ever to roam the Earth.  They are very peaceful, eating from the
tall trees and snuggling with the young.  You feel warm fuzzies
deep inside your stomach.

rooms.Name: Brontosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The tallest trees on the island are here in the Brontosaurs Paddox,
and why shouldn't they be seeing as these were the largest animals
to ever roam the Earth.  They are very peaceful, eating from the tall
trees and snuggling the young.  You feel warm fuzzies deep inside
of your stomach.

rooms.Name: Brontosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The tallest trees on the island are here in the Brontosaurs Paddox,
and why shouldn't they be seeing as they were the largest animals
to ever roam the Earth.  They are very peaceful, eating from the
tall trees and snuggling the young.  You feel warm fuzzies deep 
inside your stomach.

rooms.Name: Brontosaurs Paddox
rooms.Description:
The tallest trees on the island are here in the Brontosaurs Paddox,
and why shouldn't they be seeing as these were the largest animals
to ever roam the Earth.  They are peaceful animals, eating from the
tall trees and snuggling the young.  You feel warm fuzzies deep in
your stomach.

rooms.Name: Through The Broken Fence
rooms.Description:
You now know how , or rather what broke the fence; Raptors.
You almost lose control of your bodily functions.  This is
real fear that you are feeling.

rooms.Name: Empty Raptor Paddox
rooms.Description:
You breathe a little easier because the raptor paddox looks
like it is empty.  The foliage here is really thick and
you wonder if you really are alone.

rooms.Name: Empty T-Rex Paddox
rooms.Description:
The stench here is awful.  There are little bits of flesh all
around.  You hear the roar of the mighty TRex and tremble
uncontrolably and look around for a place to hide.

rooms.Name: Chaos
rooms.Description:
You stumble and start to roll down a hill.  You try to grab on to
passing bushes but instead rip them out of the ground.  You come to 
a cliff and 

fall
    ...down...
             ...down...
                      ...down...
                               ...down...
                                        ...down...
                                                 ...down...
                                                          ...down...


     AND BREAK YOUR NECK!!!!!!!
So sorry!

rooms.Name: Park Control Room
rooms.Description:
This is the control room for all of Jurassic Park.  This is were the imms sit
and observe.  In fact...this is our room...not yours...go away!!!  POII only!
heh..whatever...I'll work on this later!
